<TITLE> Tri-nation ODI series in Dhaka to get underway June 8 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 7 (bdnews24.com) - The Bangladesh Cricket Board Monday revealed the itinerary of the Tri-Nation One-Day International Series between hosts Bangladesh and archrivals India and Pakistan. All four matches will be played at Sher-e-Bangla National Stadium, with the top two teams playing the final on June 14 after facing each other once in the group-phase matches. The series will get underway on June 8 with hosts Bangladesh facing Pakistan, who are scheduled to arrive in Dhaka on June 6. India are scheduled to arrive on the opening day of the series, taking on archrivals Pakistan on June 10. The last group-stage match will be between the hosts and India on June 12. The organisers have kept a day in reserve for each match including the final. bd
